Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks.

Pop the ciabatta onto a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with
@olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and toss to coat well.

When the oven is hot, bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden,
~{8-10%mins}, then remove from the oven and transfer to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large baking tray. Drizzle with
@olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the
@cajun spice mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%mins}. Turn halfway
through.

While everything cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Once the croutons are done, pop the pepper onto the (now empty) baking tray.
Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast the pepper on the middle shelf until soft and slightly charred,
~{15-18%mins}.

== Dressing ==

In a large #bowl{}, mix together the @cider vinegar{30%ml}, @honey{1} and
@olive oil for the dressing{2%tbsp} (see pantry for both amounts). Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks and add to the dressing.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the
flesh out onto a board, then thinly slice widthways. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, add the Cajun sweet potato, roasted pepper,
@pea shoots{40%g} and croutons to the bowl of dressing.

Gently toss to combine.

Share your warm sweet potato salad between your #bowls{}, then fan out the
avocado in the centre of your salad.

Finish by crumbling over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} and sprinkling
with the @pumpkin seeds{15%g}.

Enjoy!